# ACT ONE

## SEQUENCE A - THE BEGINNING

### SCENE 1

= Synopsis: We meet our protagonist ALEX in their cluttered apartment. The tone is established as darkly comedic.

INT. ALEX'S APARTMENT - MORNING

FADE IN:

A cramped studio apartment. Every surface is covered with half-finished projects: model trains, sourdough starters, a disassembled motorcycle engine on the kitchen table.

ALEX (30s, perpetually disheveled, wearing yesterday's clothes) sits on the edge of the bed staring at a phone.

ALEX
(to self)
Today is the day. Today, I become a functional adult.

The phone BUZZES. Alex glances at it.

INSERT - PHONE SCREEN

A notification reads: "OVERDUE: Return library books (347 days)."

BACK TO SCENE

ALEX
(defeated)
Tomorrow. Tomorrow is the day.

Alex stands and shuffles toward the kitchen. Steps on a LEGO brick.

ALEX
AAAAAGH!

.ALEX'S KITCHEN - CONTINUOUS

Alex hops on one foot to the counter. Opens a cabinet: empty except for a single packet of hot sauce.

ALEX
(inspecting the packet)
Diablo Fire Sauce... *expired 2019*... breakfast of champions.

Alex's phone RINGS. The ringtone is an 8-bit version of Beethoven's 5th.

ALEX
(answering)
Hello?

MORGAN (V.O.)
(filtered, excited)
Alex! Get down here! I found it — I actually found it!

ALEX
Morgan, it's 7 AM. What could you possibly—

MORGAN (V.O.)
(interrupting)
The map, Alex. _The_ map. The one Grandpa always talked about.

A beat. Alex freezes mid-hop.

ALEX
...I'll be there in twenty.

> SMASH CUT TO: <

EXT. MORGAN'S ANTIQUE SHOP - DAY

A quaint storefront wedged between a laundromat and a taco stand. A hand-painted sign reads "MORGAN'S CURIOSITIES & ODDITIES — EST. 2004."

Alex BURSTS through the door.

INT. MORGAN'S ANTIQUE SHOP - CONTINUOUS

The shop is a labyrinth of shelves packed with globes, taxidermy, vintage typewriters, and things that defy categorization.

MORGAN (40s, impeccably dressed, reading glasses perched on nose) stands behind a counter, carefully unrolling a yellowed piece of parchment.

MORGAN
Close the door! The humidity will destroy it.

ALEX
(out of breath)
Is that really—

MORGAN
Seventeenth century. Portuguese cartographer. And look—
(pointing)
Right there. "Ilha do Tesouro Perdido."

ALEX
My Portuguese is rusty.

MORGAN
"Island of the Lost Treasure."

ALEX
That's... very on the nose.

MORGAN
Grandpa wasn't subtle.

They both stare at the map.

ALEX
So what do we do?

MORGAN
What do you think? **We go find it.**

Alex looks around the dusty shop. Looks down at the hot sauce packet still in hand. Looks back at Morgan.

ALEX
I've got nothing better to do.

MORGAN
That's the spirit.

They shake hands over the map.

/*
This is a boneyard comment.
It should NOT be rendered by the parser.
This entire section is ignored.

DELETED SCENE:
ALEX
I need to feed my cat first.

MORGAN
You don't have a cat.

ALEX
I might get one.
*/

CUT TO:

EXT. MARINA - SUNSET

A gorgeous golden-hour shot. Sailboats bob gently in the harbor. Seagulls wheel overhead.

ALEX and MORGAN walk along the dock carrying duffel bags.

ALEX
(looking at boats)
Please tell me it's not the one that's sinking.

MORGAN
(gesturing proudly)
That one.

He points to a 40-foot sailboat. It is, in fact, listing slightly to port. The name on the hull reads "OPTIMISM."

ALEX
"Optimism." Of course.

MORGAN
She's seaworthy. Mostly.

ALEX
"Mostly" is doing a lot of heavy lifting in that sentence.

They board the boat.

INT. SAILBOAT "OPTIMISM" - CABIN - NIGHT

A cozy but cramped cabin. Maps and charts spread across a small table. A single bare bulb swings overhead.

MORGAN
(tracing a route on a nautical chart)
We sail south along the coast, then cut west past the archipelago. Three days, maybe four.

ALEX
And then?

MORGAN
And then we find out if Grandpa was crazy or a genius.

ALEX
Those aren't mutually exclusive.

MORGAN
(smiling)
No. No, they're not.

~Bon Voyage

Alex picks up an old PHOTOGRAPH from the shelf. It shows their grandfather standing on a tropical beach, grinning, holding a shovel.

ALEX (CONT'D)
(quietly)
What did you find out there, old man?

EXT. OPEN OCEAN - DAY (MONTAGE)

.. title card: "DAY ONE" ..

- Alex struggling with ropes, getting tangled.
- Morgan at the helm, looking competent and serene.
- A pod of DOLPHINS racing alongside the boat.
- Alex attempting to cook, producing something that smokes ominously.
- Morgan tossing Alex's creation overboard. A seagull catches it and immediately drops it.

.. title card: "DAY TWO" ..

- Rain. Lots of rain.
- Alex bailing water with a coffee mug.
- Morgan laughing.
- A rainbow breaking through the clouds.
- Alex and Morgan sharing a flask, watching the sunset.

END MONTAGE.

EXT. OPEN OCEAN - DAY THREE - DAWN

The boat cuts through calm, crystal-clear water. In the distance: a lush green island rising from the sea like a dream.

ALEX
(whispered)
Morgan... look.

Morgan emerges from below deck, rubbing sleep from their eyes. Sees the island. Drops the coffee cup.

MORGAN
That's it. That's the island.

ALEX
(grinning)
Grandpa wasn't crazy.

MORGAN
(grinning back)
Jury's still out on genius.

They sail toward the island.

FADE TO:

## SEQUENCE B - THE ISLAND

### SCENE 2

EXT. ISLAND BEACH - DAY

The boat anchored offshore. Alex and Morgan wade through shallow turquoise water to a white sand beach. Dense jungle beyond.

A figure emerges from the tree line.

@McCALLISTER
(cheerfully)
Took you long enough! I've been waiting thirty years!

McCALLISTER (60s, weathered, wild-haired, barefoot, wearing a tattered Hawaiian shirt) raises a hand in greeting.

Alex and Morgan exchange a look.

ALEX
(sotto voce)
Did Grandpa mention anyone else knowing about this place?

MORGAN
(sotto voce)
No. No, he did not.

McCALLISTER
(approaching)
You must be the Reeves grandkids! Got the look. Got the look right in the eyes.
(beat)
Well? You coming or not? Treasure's not gonna find itself!

He turns and walks back into the jungle without waiting for a response.

ALEX
(to Morgan)
On a scale of one to ten, how murdered are we about to be?

MORGAN
(already following McCallister)
Only one way to find out.

INT. JUNGLE PATH - DAY

Dense foliage. Bird calls. Shafts of light cutting through the canopy.

McCallister leads, machete in hand, cutting a path with practiced ease. Alex and Morgan follow.

McCALLISTER
(not looking back)
Your grandpa and I served together. Navy. '62. He saved my life twice — once from a torpedo, once from a bad oyster.

ALEX
A bad oyster?

McCALLISTER
Allergic. Throat closed up like a— well, anyway. He found this island on shore leave. Said there was something here. Something old. Something ***valuable***.

MORGAN
And he told you about it?

McCALLISTER
Told me to guard it. So I did. Built a shack. Caught fish. Waited.
(turning to face them)
He said his grandkids would come someday. And here you are.

ALEX
Here we are.

A long silence. The jungle hums around them.

McCALLISTER
(suddenly bright)
Anyway! The cave's just up ahead. Watch out for the drop — it's a doozy!

He disappears around a bend.

ALEX
(to Morgan)
I've changed my answer. Eleven.

> FADE OUT. <

# ACT TWO

## SEQUENCE C - THE CAVE

INT. CAVE ENTRANCE - DAY

ALEX
I'm not going in there.

MORGAN ^
We have to go in there.

They stare at each other. Alex blinks first.

ALEX
(whispering)
What if there are bats?

MORGAN ^
(confident)
Then we'll have company.

McCALLISTER
(from inside the cave)
There are definitely bats!

ALEX
(to Morgan)
Great. Wonderful.

MORGAN ^
(grinning)
Think of it as an adventure.

ALEX
Fine.

McCallister lights a TORCH and leads them inside.

INT. CAVE - DEEP INTERIOR - CONTINUOUS

The cave opens into a massive underground chamber. Stalactites hang from the ceiling like chandeliers. A subterranean river cuts through the center.

And there, on a natural stone pedestal illuminated by a shaft of light from a crack in the ceiling above—

A WOODEN CHEST.

ALEX
(breathless)
No way.

MORGAN
(breathless)
Way.

McCALLISTER
(matter-of-fact)
Told you.

They approach the chest slowly, reverently.

MORGAN
(reaching for the lid)
Ready?

ALEX
Born ready.

Morgan opens the chest. Golden light spills out.

Inside: not gold, not jewels, but hundreds of leather-bound JOURNALS. Filled cover to cover with writings, diagrams, sketches of plants, animals, constellations.

ALEX (CONT'D)
(confused)
Books? The treasure is... books?

McCALLISTER
(quietly)
Knowledge. The greatest treasure there is.

Morgan picks up a journal. Opens it carefully. Eyes go wide.

MORGAN
Alex... these are scientific observations. Detailed, meticulous records of species that don't exist in any database. This island...
(looking up)
This island is undiscovered. These records — they could change everything we know about marine biology, botany, zoology—

ALEX
(slowly understanding)
Grandpa wasn't looking for gold.

MORGAN
He was looking for something better.

A beat.

ALEX
(to McCallister)
You've been guarding _scientific journals_ for thirty years?

McCALLISTER
(shrugging)
Best job I ever had.

They all laugh. The sound echoes through the cave.

ALEX
(picking up a journal)
Well then... let's get reading.

They sit in the cave, surrounded by decades of discovery, and begin to read.

FADE OUT.


> THE END <
